      "content": "thanks for the tip on the smart pointers, i'll check the destructor logic in the `log_store` class specifically. \n\nthe hardware is pretty tight so i can't really run a profiler on the target. i'm mostly stuck with just looking at heap usage via the serial console and basic logs. when i look at the heap, it's just a constant, slow upward slope. it's not like a sudden spike, just this persistent creep. \n\nif i can't use Valgrind or ASan, what are some manual \"instrumentation\" techniques i can use to see which specific objects are hanging around? i need to know if it's the `DataLog` objects themselves or if something else is being allocated inside the `push_back` or `remove_oldest` calls.",
